text: Clipper is an unincorporated community in Whatcom County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Clipper was established in 1901, and remained in operation until 1955. The community took its name from the Clipper Shingle Company. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Whatcom County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Clipper, Washington
